Preheat your oven to 200°C. Trim the @aubergine{1} then halve lengthways. Chop each half into four
long strips, then chop widthways into roughly 2cm pieces. Pick the @rosemary{½}(finely chopped, stalks
removed) leaves from their stalks, finely chop (discard the stalks). Pop the aubergine onto a
#baking tray{}, drizzle with @oil{} and sprinkle on half the rosemary and a good pinch of @salt{}.
Toss to coat. Roast on the top shelf of the oven until soft and golden, ~{20-25%minutes}, turning
halfway.

Pour the @water{300}(for the rice) into a #saucepan{} and bring to the boil. When boiling, stir in the
@basmati rice{150}, lower the heat to medium and pop a #lid{} on the pan. Leave to cook for
~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another
~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Pop the @British beef mince{240} into a #mixing bowl{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add the
@panko breadcrumbs{10}, @blue cheese{30}(crumbled), the remaining rosemary and @water{2%tbsp}. Mix
well and then shape the mixture into 4 even-sized balls. TIP: Make sure the meatballs are well formed
by rolling them in the palm of your hand. This will make sure they don't fall apart.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} over medium-high heat. When hot, add the meatballs
and brown all over, ~{3-4%minutes}, turning frequently. Lower the heat and add the
@finely chopped tomatoes with basil{1}. Cover the pan with a lid or foil and simmer until the
meatballs are cooked through, ~{7-8%minutes} stirring halfway.

> IMPORTANT: The meatballs are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When the meatballs are cooked, remove the lid and if needed, simmer until the sauce has thickened
slightly, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in the aubergine when it is cooked and get ready to serve!

Fluff the rice up with a #fork{} and share between your plates. Top with the meatballs and then the
sauce. Tuck in!